==English==
===Etymology===
L. acer sharp; prob. assimilated in form to acid. See {Eager}

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæk.ɹɪd/
*{{audio|en-us-acrid.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
# Sharp and [[harsh]], or [[bitter]] and not, to the taste; [[pungent]].
#:'''''acrid''' salts''
# Causing [[heat]] and [[irritation]]; [[corrosive]]
#:'''''acrid''' secretions''
# [[caustic|Caustic]]; [[bitter]]; bitterly irritating
#:'''''acrid''' temper, mind, writing''

